{"type":"step-attempt","step":"design","sessionId":"0e654c19-8979-4d39-adf4-a5acbb34c7ad","outcome":{"verdict":"success","findingsPath":null,"error":null,"toolResult":{"ok":true,"reason":"Wrote design.md, spec.md, tasks.md under specrunner/changes/approval-revision-binding/ for the approval-revision-binding feature (branch change/approval-revision-binding-c60285d5).\n\nCore design (verified against current code):\n- D1/D3: Replace conformanceApprovedLatest (verdict-only, reverification.ts:67-72) with a state-pure guard that additionally requires latest-conformance.commitOid === latest-verification.commitOid; missing commitOid → false (fail-closed → code-review re-entry). Applies to both STANDARD (types.ts:250) and FAST (types.ts:307) profiles.\n- D2 (load-bearing): Stamp verification (CLI step) StepRun.commitOid at step ENTRY, not exit — because propagateVerificationResult (propagate.ts:50-69) git-commits the result file inside step.run() and moves worktree HEAD. Entry HEAD == conformance's recorded commitOid in the true reverify path (nothing commits between conformance→verification), so no-change → match (criterion 2); re-run/build-fixer moves HEAD → mismatch (criterion 1).\n- D4: Surfaced deliberate consequence — build-fixer committing after conformance-approval now re-enters the reviewer chain (updates existing TC-003/004/019). code-fixer-before-conformance path stays short-circuited.\n- D5: Corrected the request's premise — approvedAtCommit already holds a real value (applyRoundResults + parallel-review-round.ts, contract-fixed by 2026-07-15 as \"reviewed source revision\"). The real gap is selectPendingMembers has no revision check. Added baselineCommit param + coordinator re-anchor of source-path-untouched approved members to preserve source-scoped invalidation (req 7) without regressing the 2026-07-15 optimization.\n- D6: Legacy/missing commitOid → stale (fail-closed), mirroring achieved-assurance.ts prior art (the archive-time analog of this routing-time gate).\n\nEnumerated all affected existing tests (criterion 6) in design + tasks. Flagged the D5 re-anchor scope as the main Open Question for code-review. No source (src/) edits performed — plan only.","status":"success"},"followUpAttempts":0,"transientRetryAttempts":0,"addedTurns":{"reportRetry":0,"postWork":0,"outputRepair":0}},"startedAt":"2026-07-21T10:22:46.527Z","endedAt":"2026-07-21T10:46:55.401Z","commitOid":"b8d2031000ebb55228a49f147f6a6feda98eaa8b"}
